title: Virat Kohli
text: Virat Kohli (born 5 November 1988) is an Indian international cricketer and the former captain of the Indian national cricket team who plays as a right-handed batsman for Royal Challengers Bangalore in the IPL and for the Delhi in Indian domestic cricket.

title: Virat Kohli
text:
International Career
In August 2008, Kohli was selected for inclusion in the ODl squad for the tour of Sri Lanka and the Champions Trophy in Pakistan. Prior to the Sri Lankan tour, Kohli had limited experience, with only eight List A matches under his belt.

title: Virat Kohli
text:
IPL Career
After a successful performance in the Under-19 World Cup, Kohli was signed by the Royal Challengers Bangalore for a sum of $30,000 as a part youth contract. He was the captain of the franchise for 8 seasons but was futile in winning trophies.
